# CHIP v2 blackwell-sm-ports
Full Name: NVIDIA Blackwell Streaming Multiprocessor (Port-Level)
Description:
A textual representation of a streaming multiprocessor using port-level and memory-aware connectivity.
Architecture Goals:
- Express the SM as composable modules
- Demonstrate port-level connectivity
- Keep parsing deterministic and auditable
Modules:
Define module Warp Scheduler:
Summary: Issues work to active warps.
Operations: select, issue, stall
Inputs: warp_state, ready_mask
Outputs: selected_warp, issue_decision
Define module Tensor Core:
Summary: Executes matrix-oriented tensor operations.
Operations: mma, accumulate, convert
Inputs: operand_a, operand_b, accumulator
Outputs: result_fragment
Define module Register File:
Summary: Stores per-thread register state.
Operations: read, write, allocate
Inputs: write_value, register_index, thread_id
Outputs: read_value, allocation_status
Instantiate:
Create 4 instances of Warp Scheduler
Create 8 instances of Tensor Core
Create 1 instances of Register File
Connect:
Warp Scheduler.selected_warp -> Tensor Core.operand_a
Tensor Core.result_fragment -> Register File.write_value
Register File.read_value -> Shared Memory.write
Memory:
Shared Memory: 256 KB
Output: Port-level SM tile with scheduling, tensor execution, register storage, and memory access.
